               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the donors; incipits of the sections and chapters; numbers of the chapters; the word mǝʿǝraf; elements of the punctuation signs, Ethiopic numerals; element of the quires marks; ruling lines in the Canon tables. &#xD;
On the incipit page of each Gospel, a few lines are rubricated (two red line alternating with black ones).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Lists of "tituli" for Gospels of Matthew and Luke are missing.</note>
                     <note>- The scribe highlighted some chapters using line break after the chapter number, before its incipit (s. e.g., fols. 18va, 21r)</note>
                     <note>- Streched rubricated script is used for some passages in the Introduction and the Biblical text, s. fols. 141ra, 14<ref type="mss" corresp="ES2vb143">2vb-143</ref>ra, etc.</note>
                     <note>- For the Introductions, Biographies of the Evangelists etc., smaller script is used.</note>
                     <note>Erasures and corrections are in fol. 8.</note>
                     <note>The "Biography of Matthew" is misplaced: it is merged with the part "On the reliability of the Gospels", and precedes the Canon tables.</note>
                     <note>Additional leaves with miniatures were infixed in the recent time, to "illuminate" the Ms.</note>
                     <note>Decorated quire marks.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Decorated quire marks are written in the upper margin, left corner of the folios.</note>
                     <note>Red threads are inserted in the upper right corners of some folios, for navigation.</note>
                  </msItem>
